Here fa=A(x) is the parton distribution, N is a normalization factor so that ! 1 ?= 1. An observable can be constructed with the three momenta p, PH and k. One can also use instead of k the one observed in the laborotry frame. Any experimental cuts can be implemented into (5.2). These cuts are not only due to experiment for clean signal, but also are necessary in order to select the kinematical region where our perturbative results can be applied. For this purpose we use a simple cut. We require that the transversal momentum of O/1 to be larger than PT . With sufficient large PT one can be in confident that the employment of parton model is correct. With this cut the contribution from elastic/diffractive production is discarded, only inelastic production which is handled in this work contributes to the process (5.1). With the cut the factor N is the total crosssection of unpolarized O/1. We will take O/1 to be a charmonium O/c1 and the initial hadron A in (5.1) is a proton. For parton distributions we simply take the HO set given in [16] with _ = MO/c1 . We take MH = MO/c1 = 3:51Gev and ffs(MO/c1 ) = 0:25. The cut is PT = 3GeV. We consider here the total cross-section oeflp(O/c1). The cross-section is proportional to the nonperturbative constant a(8) in our approximation. An estimation of this constant in another convention is given in [2] and in [17]. The relation to the parameter H 08 defined in [2,3] is:

a(8) = 12 M 3O/c

